# claude-watch default cron entries.
#
# Baked into the image at /etc/cron.d/cw-default. These entries run
# inside every container deployment by default — they don't reference
# host-specific paths, host-specific tools, or operator-specific
# state. Anything operator-specific (PR-watch loops, custom event
# emitters, etc.) belongs in /etc/cron.d/private, which is reserved
# for operator bind-mounts (see container/compose.yml).
#
# Why bake these specifically: every claude-watch deployment wants
# active-agents.json (the queue-minisite and friends consume it) and
# the metrics emit (work-queue-exporter scrapes the Prom-style
# textfile). Without these baked, every host needed separate cron
# setup — painful on macOS Docker Desktop especially (LaunchAgents,
# Full Disk Access prompts).
#
# Format: m h dom mon dow user command
#   - user MUST be `hndrewaall` (uid 1000); the cron daemon runs as
#     root but setuid's into the user named in each crontab line.
#   - claude-watch is on PATH for uid 1000 (image-baked
#     /usr/local/bin/claude-watch).
#   - State file path /var/lib/claude-watch/active-agents.json
#     matches the in-container path that's backed by the
#     `claude-watch-state` named volume (or the CW_STATE_PATH host
#     bind-mount, when set) — same path either way.
#   - stderr from claude-watch goes to /tmp/claude-watch-cron-*.log
#     so operators can inspect failures via
#     `docker compose exec <c> cat /tmp/claude-watch-cron-*.log`.

# Publish active-agents JSON state file (queue_id + alive per subagent)
# every minute. Consumers: work-queue-exporter (Prom has_live_owner
# gauge), queue-minisite (owner-status column), cron-queue-check.
* * * * *   hndrewaall /usr/local/bin/claude-watch active-agents --json --write-state /var/lib/claude-watch/active-agents.json > /dev/null 2>>/tmp/claude-watch-cron-active-agents.log

# Emit Prometheus-style metrics every minute. logger writes to syslog
# (or stderr inside the container — cron's -L 15 flag routes stderr to
# the supervisor log).
* * * * *   hndrewaall /usr/local/bin/claude-watch metrics > /tmp/claude-watch-cron-metrics.log 2>&1

# Stale-ready queue-item watchdog. Every 5 minutes, scan
# `session-task queue ready --json` for pending items that have been
# ready past the threshold (default 6 minutes) and emit ONE aggregated
# `queue-stale-ready` claude-event per qualifying tick. Single-emit per
# queue id (ledger at /var/lib/claude-watch/stale-ready-state.json), so
# a long-stuck item only triggers once until it leaves the queue.
# Silent exit when nothing qualifies — no console spam.
*/5 * * * *  hndrewaall /usr/local/bin/claude-watch stale-ready-check > /tmp/claude-watch-cron-stale-ready.log 2>&1
